docs.abstract: Embracing intellectual diversity means being brave enough to consider ideas and practices that might inspire you to change your life.
docs.snippet: Embracing intellectual diversity means being brave enough to consider ideas and practices that might inspire you to change your life.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last week news outlets and social media were abuzz with the announcement of plans to establish a university dedicated to the “fearless pursuit of truth” and “forbidden courses.” The new school, the University of Austin — not to be confused with the fully accredited public University of Texas at Austin — is being created by a group of moderate and conservative intellectuals and writers who are frequently critical of what they see as groupthink on college campuses. Higher education, they argue, has been broken for a long time, and this school is an attempt to begin to fix it.

headline.main: Anxiety About Wokeness Is Intellectual Weakness

docs.abstract: Republicans ran up the margins in rural Virginia counties, the latest sign that Democrats, as one lawmaker put it, “continue to tank in small-town America.”
docs.snippet: Republicans ran up the margins in rural Virginia counties, the latest sign that Democrats, as one lawmaker put it, “continue to tank in small-town America.”
docs.lead_paragraph: HOT SPRINGS, Va. — The increasingly liberal politics of Virginia had been a sore spot for residents of this conservative town of 499 people nestled in the Allegheny Mountains. But this past week, as Republicans stormed to marquee victories powered in part by turnout in rural areas like Bath County, local voters cheered.

headline.main: Democrats Thought They Bottomed Out in Rural, White America. It Wasn’t the Bottom.
headline.print_headline: In Rural Areas, Prospects Sink For Democrats

docs.abstract: The Mexico City curator Magalí Arriola will again assemble Meridians at Art Basel Miami Beach, a diverting lineup of hard-to-fit pieces.
docs.snippet: The Mexico City curator Magalí Arriola will again assemble Meridians at Art Basel Miami Beach, a diverting lineup of hard-to-fit pieces.
docs.lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Art Basel had practical purposes in mind when it introduced the Meridians section to its sprawling Miami Beach marketplace in 2019. The oversize exhibition space was meant to make room for large-scale objects and performance pieces that galleries could not fit in their standard fair booths.

headline.main: A Curator Makes Room for Big Ideas and Big Art

docs.abstract: How five fashion friends got a starring role fighting discrimination and hate in a new comic book series.
docs.snippet: How five fashion friends got a starring role fighting discrimination and hate in a new comic book series.
docs.lead_paragraph: One evening, just before Halloween, a party was held at Chinese Tuxedo, a trendy Cantonese restaurant in Chinatown in Manhattan. Attendees entered through a back alley lit by yellow lanterns, past graffitied walls covered in posters of superheroes. Inside they sipped Champagne while Asian drag queens, West Dakota, Panthera Lush and Dynasty, writhed around the restaurant’s poles. The evening’s invitation had dictated: “Dress to Slay.”

headline.main: The Superheroes From House of Slay Are Here to Stay
headline.print_headline: House of Slay’s Stars Step Out
